So when Manny Machado hit the market, they acquire him as a rental, at a very modest cost in prospects. Mookie Betts? Again acquired at a very modest prospect cost. Scherzer/Turner? They traded Ruiz/Josiah Gray. Both are good, but the Dodgers had other options at those spots.

And they also develop international signees (Diego Cartaya/Keibert Ruiz/Miguel Vargas, etc.). 

Put it all together and the Dodgers have continually had the prospects to be involved in any deadline deal they want to consider.

And since then they've picked Gavin Lux/Michael Busch/Bobby Miller, all of whom are quite valuable in trade talks. They've also developed Gavin Stone/Alex Verdugo/Ryan Pepiot/Dustin May/Tony Gonsolin with later round picks.

The Dodgers haven't been perfect in drafting, but time after time, they have found stars in the back of the first round: Corey Seager (18th pick, 2012), Walker Buehler (24th pick, 2015), Will Smith (32nd pick, 2016).
